Lovely video, Love the fans that are showing actual support and being patient

but there are some of you that have been negative despite knowing her mental health and struggles
If you are a Gura fan, why are you pretending to not be one and pretending mental health and physical health
is not affected in any way in an idol? 

Some of you have been bullying and harassing her
and isn't that why she took a mental break in the first place? She comes back only to be met with her own fans taking pot-shots at her.
You're saying she abandoned you but no, you're abandoning her. She came here to be an idol, she wanted people to have fun, let people know they're not alone,
that they have others out there as well. She supported you, your mental health, spoke to you, tried to lift you up when you were down...
But what are some of you doing?
You are doing the opposite to her, not even worried if she is okay, not worried if she's going through anything and forgetting that behind her character is just a person...
that person is human, she has feelings and she is dealing with bullies and issues.
Why are you, as a fan, becoming so overly parasocial that her whole life is only to please you at any moment?
What if she had family issues? What if she got into an accident? What if her internet went out and she can't stream?
Shouldn't you be more accepting of her humanity, her well being, her safety as her fans?
